NHL Thrashers Said to Be Sold, Will Be Moved to Winnipeg From Atlanta

-- B y   M i c h a e l   B u t e a u
-- 
2011-05-31T15:44:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/nhl-thrashers-said-to-be-sold-will-be-moved-to-winnipeg-from-atlanta.html
The  Atlanta Thrashers  will move to
 Canada  after being sold to Winnipeg, Manitoba-based True North
Sports & Entertainment Ltd., according to a team official who
spoke on the condition of anonymity.  Rob Koch, a spokesman for the Thrashers, and  Scott Brown , a  spokesman for True North, declined to comment. The official
would not be named because an announcement is scheduled to be
made at a news conference today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Buteau in Atlanta at 
 mbuteau@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  